<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 19 at 2:48PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL HUNTINGDON COUNTY
THROUGH 315 PM EDT...
At 248 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Huntingdon, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Huntingdon, Mount Union, Raystown Dam, Shy Beaver, Trough Creek State
Park, Entriken, McConnellstown, Mapleton, Mill Creek, Kistler,
Marklesburg, Cassville and Juniata College.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
